node.text:
Sunday Morning cheesy toast with @rosehoneyp 

RECIPE: 
3 eggs
3/4 cup cheddar cheese, grated(we used kerrygold from costco)
1/2 cup ricotta cheese(we used kite hill almond cheese)
Butter
6 slices of bread
Salt & pepper

Preheat broiler to medium. Meanwhile, whisk the eggs in a large bowl then add the cheddar, ricotta, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and a few cracks of pepper. Mix well. 

Spread some butter on each slice of bread and then top with the egg mixture. Broil for 6-10 minutes, or until deep golden brown. The tomato juice is made by blending whole canned san marzano tomatoes with 1 teaspoon of salt and enough water to make it loose and pourable. Enjoy!
